2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking): The paper proposes a block processing FDE technique for CP-free transmission schemes in massive MIMO systems. This falls under the domain of communications and networking. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not explicitly deal with social networks, but the proposed technique can be applied to improve the performance of wireless networks, which can be considered as a type of social network. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves the optimization of block length for FDE, which can be considered as an algorithmic problem. However, this is not the main focus of the paper, hence it is less likely to belong to this sub-category.
